@PMSBackend_HostAddress = http://localhost:7000
@accessToken = 
@refreshToken = 

### Variables are automatically saved in this file for Postman/REST Client

### 0. Generate Token Directly (Quick Testing - Bypass Login)
POST {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Auth/generate-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1
}

### 1. Login - Get Access Token and Refresh Token (Super Admin)
POST {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Auth/Login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "superadmin",
  "authType": 1,
  "password": "1234"
}

### 1b. Login as Admin
POST {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Auth/Login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "admin",
  "authType": 1,
  "password": "1234"
}

### 1c. Login as Entry User
POST {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Auth/Login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "entryuser",
  "authType": 1,
  "password": "1234"
}

### 2. Login with Mobile Auth (OTP-based)
POST {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Auth/Login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "+1234567890",
  "authType": 2
}

### 3. Verify OTP (Use after mobile login)
POST {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "otp": "Abc@1234"
}

### 4. Refresh Token - Get new access token
POST {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "{{accessToken}}",
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 5. Revoke Token - Logout from specific device
POST {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Auth/revoke-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 6. Revoke All User Tokens - Logout from all devices
POST {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Auth/revoke-all-user-tokens
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1
}

### 7. Example: Use token in a protected endpoint (GET Users)
GET {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/User
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 8. Example: Dashboard endpoint with token
GET {{PMSBackend_HostAddress}}/api/Dashboard/patient-count
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### User IDs Reference:
### Super Admin - UserId: 1
### Admin - UserId: 2
